{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-02",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_02_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Death in the Fog",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 5,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 975.02,
  "page_end_sec": 1216.3,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.738,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 975.02,
      "end": 977.22,
      "text": "His eyes became narrow and sultry."
    },
    {
      "start": 977.4,
      "end": 979.16,
      "text": "His voice came out deep"
    },
    {
      "start": 979.7,
      "end": 980.43,
      "text": "as the Lieutenant's."
    },
    {
      "start": 980.82,
      "end": 982.1,
      "text": "\"I don't like this."
    },
    {
      "start": 982.78,
      "end": 984.22,
      "text": "What are you sucking around for?"
    },
    {
      "start": 984.47,
      "end": 985.12,
      "text": "Tell me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 985.44,
      "end": 987.14,
      "text": "or get out and let me go to bed.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 988.672,
      "end": 989.7,
      "text": "\"Who's Thursby?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 989.88,
      "end": 990.76,
      "text": "Dundy demanded."
    },
    {
      "start": 991.56,
      "end": 993.8,
      "text": "\"I told Tom what I knew about him.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 994.14,
      "end": 996.46,
      "text": "\"You told Tom damned little.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 996.66,
      "end": 998.94,
      "text": "\"I knew damned little.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 999.92,
      "end": 1001.16,
      "text": "\"Why were you tailing him?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1002.272,
      "end": 1003.38,
      "text": "\"I wasn't.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1003.4,
      "end": 1004.28,
      "text": "Miles was—"
    },
    {
      "start": 1005.12,
      "end": 1007.88,
      "text": "for the swell reason that we had a client who was"
    },
    {
      "start": 1007.88,
      "end": 1011.28,
      "text": "paying good United States money to have him tailed.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1012.22,
      "end": 1012.65,
      "text": "\"Who's the client?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1014.08,
      "end": 1016.44,
      "text": "Placidity came back to Spade's face and voice.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1016.62,
      "end": 1018.11,
      "text": "He said reprovingly:"
    },
    {
      "start": 1018.92,
      "end": 1020.38,
      "text": "\"You know I can't tell you that until"
    },
    {
      "start": 1020.38,
      "end": 1021.76,
      "text": "I've talked it over with the client.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1022.944,
      "end": 1023.94,
      "text": "\"You'll tell it to me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1024.44,
      "end": 1025.7,
      "text": "or you'll tell it in court,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1025.98,
      "end": 1027.22,
      "text": "Dundy said hotly."
    },
    {
      "start": 1028.08,
      "end": 1028.68,
      "text": "\"This is murder"
    },
    {
      "start": 1028.84,
      "end": 1030.06,
      "text": "and don't you forget it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1030.94,
      "end": 1031.4,
      "text": "\"Maybe.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1032.0,
      "end": 1034.04,
      "text": "And here's something for you to not forget,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1034.2,
      "end": 1034.54,
      "text": "sweetheart."
    },
    {
      "start": 1035.44,
      "end": 1036.04,
      "text": "I'll tell it"
    },
    {
      "start": 1036.04,
      "end": 1036.64,
      "text": "or not"
    },
    {
      "start": 1036.76,
      "end": 1037.84,
      "text": "as I damned please."
    },
    {
      "start": 1038.74,
      "end": 1040.14,
      "text": "It's a long while since I burst out"
    },
    {
      "start": 1040.14,
      "end": 1042.0,
      "text": "crying because policemen didn't like me.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1042.944,
      "end": 1045.18,
      "text": "Tom left the sofa and sat on the foot of the bed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1046.1,
      "end": 1047.28,
      "text": "His carelessly shaven"
    },
    {
      "start": 1047.28,
      "end": 1049.1,
      "text": "mud-smeared face was tired and lined."
    },
    {
      "start": 1049.44,
      "end": 1050.78,
      "text": "\"Be reasonable,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1050.92,
      "end": 1051.14,
      "text": "Sam,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1051.38,
      "end": 1051.96,
      "text": "he pleaded."
    },
    {
      "start": 1052.58,
      "end": 1053.4,
      "text": "\"Give us a chance."
    },
    {
      "start": 1054.36,
      "end": 1056.4,
      "text": "How can we turn up anything on Miles's killing"
    },
    {
      "start": 1056.84,
      "end": 1058.46,
      "text": "if you won't give us what you've got?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1059.6,
      "end": 1061.04,
      "text": "\"You needn't get a headache over that,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1061.728,
      "end": 1062.44,
      "text": "Spade told him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1063.04,
      "end": 1064.02,
      "text": "\"I'll bury my dead.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1065.28,
      "end": 1068.02,
      "text": "Lieutenant Dundy sat down and put his hands on his knees again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1068.78,
      "end": 1069.6,
      "text": "His eyes were warm"
    },
    {
      "start": 1069.64,
      "end": 1070.34,
      "text": "green discs."
    },
    {
      "start": 1071.44,
      "end": 1072.14,
      "text": "\"I thought you would,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1072.42,
      "end": 1072.8,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1073.6,
      "end": 1074.78,
      "text": "He smiled with grim content."
    },
    {
      "start": 1075.84,
      "end": 1077.68,
      "text": "\"That's just exactly why we came to see you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1077.76,
      "end": 1078.46,
      "text": "isn't it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1078.48,
      "end": 1078.68,
      "text": "Tom?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1080.0,
      "end": 1081.88,
      "text": "Tom groaned, but said nothing articulate.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1083.232,
      "end": 1084.78,
      "text": "Spade watched Dundy warily.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1086.06,
      "end": 1088.86,
      "text": "\"That's just exactly what I said to Tom,\" the Lieutenant went on.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1089.28,
      "end": 1089.58,
      "text": "\"I said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 1089.6,
      "end": 1089.9,
      "text": "'Tom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1090.3,
      "end": 1092.48,
      "text": "I've got a hunch that Sam Spade's a man"
    },
    {
      "start": 1092.48,
      "end": 1094.36,
      "text": "to keep the family-troubles in the family."
    },
    {
      "start": 1094.98,
      "end": 1096.34,
      "text": "That's just what I said to him.'\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1097.34,
      "end": 1099.1,
      "text": "The wariness went out of Spade's eyes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1099.52,
      "end": 1101.44,
      "text": "He made his eyes dull with boredom."
    },
    {
      "start": 1102.1,
      "end": 1105.46,
      "text": "He turned his face around to Tom and asked with great carelessness:"
    },
    {
      "start": 1106.464,
      "end": 1107.98,
      "text": "\"What's itching your boy-friend now?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1109.088,
      "end": 1110.74,
      "text": "Dundy jumped up and tapped Spade's",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1110.74,
      "end": 1112.72,
      "text": "chest with the ends of two bent fingers."
    },
    {
      "start": 1113.8,
      "end": 1114.48,
      "text": "\"Just this,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1114.74,
      "end": 1115.36,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1115.7,
      "end": 1117.84,
      "text": "taking pains to make each word distinct,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1118.688,
      "end": 1120.86,
      "text": "emphasizing them with his tapping finger-ends:"
    },
    {
      "start": 1121.76,
      "end": 1124.94,
      "text": "\"Thursby was shot down in front of his hotel"
    },
    {
      "start": 1124.94,
      "end": 1128.66,
      "text": "just thirty-five minutes after you left Burritt Street.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1129.76,
      "end": 1130.22,
      "text": "Spade spoke,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1130.4,
      "end": 1132.14,
      "text": "taking equal pains with his words:"
    },
    {
      "start": 1132.96,
      "end": 1136.12,
      "text": "\"Keep your God-damned paws off me.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1137.11,
      "end": 1139.14,
      "text": "Dundy withdrew the tapping fingers,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1139.58,
      "end": 1141.1,
      "text": "but there was no change in his voice:"
    },
    {
      "start": 1142.08,
      "end": 1144.28,
      "text": "\"Tom says you were in too much of a hurry"
    },
    {
      "start": 1144.28,
      "end": 1146.26,
      "text": "to even stop for a look at your partner.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1147.52,
      "end": 1148.84,
      "text": "Tom growled apologetically:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1149.72,
      "end": 1149.92,
      "text": "\"Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1150.1,
      "end": 1150.8,
      "text": "damn it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1150.8,
      "end": 1151.02,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1151.26,
      "end": 1153.02,
      "text": "you did run off like that.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1154.1,
      "end": 1156.32,
      "text": "\"And you didn't go to Archer's house to tell his wife,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1156.54,
      "end": 1157.44,
      "text": "the Lieutenant said."
    },
    {
      "start": 1158.2,
      "end": 1160.46,
      "text": "\"We called up and that girl in your office was there,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1160.54,
      "end": 1162.06,
      "text": "and she said you sent her.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1162.976,
      "end": 1163.82,
      "text": "Spade nodded.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1163.84,
      "end": 1166.08,
      "text": "His face was stupid in its calmness."
    },
    {
      "start": 1167.12,
      "end": 1170.18,
      "text": "Lieutenant Dundy raised his two bent fingers towards Spade's chest,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1170.36,
      "end": 1171.36,
      "text": "quickly lowered them, and"
    },
    {
      "start": 1171.36,
      "end": 1171.64,
      "text": "said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 1171.78,
      "end": 1174.2,
      "text": "\"I give you ten minutes to get to a phone"
    },
    {
      "start": 1174.88,
      "end": 1176.2,
      "text": "and do your talking to the girl."
    },
    {
      "start": 1176.48,
      "end": 1177.44,
      "text": "I give you ten"
    },
    {
      "start": 1177.52,
      "end": 1178.94,
      "text": "minutes to get to Thursby's joint—"
    },
    {
      "start": 1179.14,
      "end": 1179.62,
      "text": "Geary,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1179.78,
      "end": 1180.52,
      "text": "near Leavenworth."
    },
    {
      "start": 1181.0,
      "end": 1182.86,
      "text": "You could do it easy in that time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1183.14,
      "end": 1184.4,
      "text": "or fifteen at the most,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1184.8,
      "end": 1186.02,
      "text": "and that gives you ten or fifteen"
    },
    {
      "start": 1186.02,
      "end": 1187.96,
      "text": "minutes of waiting before he showed up.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1188.62,
      "end": 1189.9,
      "text": "\"I knew where he lived?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1190.1,
      "end": 1191.0,
      "text": "Spade asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 1191.7,
      "end": 1193.98,
      "text": "\"And I knew he hadn't gone straight home from killing Miles?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1194.85,
      "end": 1196.46,
      "text": "\"You knew what you knew,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1196.66,
      "end": 1197.98,
      "text": "Dundy replied stubbornly."
    },
    {
      "start": 1198.64,
      "end": 1200.04,
      "text": "\"What time did you get home?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1201.24,
      "end": 1202.18,
      "text": "\"Twenty minutes to four.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1202.58,
      "end": 1204.16,
      "text": "I walked around thinking things over.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1205.22,
      "end": 1207.44,
      "text": "The Lieutenant wagged his round head up and down.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1208.42,
      "end": 1209.86,
      "text": "\"We knew you weren't home at three-thirty."
    },
    {
      "start": 1210.56,
      "end": 1211.78,
      "text": "We tried to get you on the phone."
    },
    {
      "start": 1212.736,
      "end": 1213.78,
      "text": "Where'd you do your walking?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 1214.68,
      "end": 1215.34,
      "text": "\"Out Bush Street",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1215.52,
      "end": 1216.3,
      "text": "a way and back.\""
    }
  ]
}